 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Narben</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Ain't going to happen.<BR>Why?<BR>Blame wizzies and druids :) (I'll explain)</P><P>All of the player illusions are stored in the global file, this allows them to be shown to everyone in every zone in the game. The size of this file is limited because the bigger it is the more system memory it uses up (directly related to your graphics card I believe, at least it used to be). Verant is very careful about what they put into this file because every extra animation they add uses up more system resources. With the introduction of Luclin they added multiple extra illusions - the 3 wolf forms, the imp and the small drake familiars. In order to make room for these animations they removed the 2 different skeleton forms (white and dark) and replaced them with a single look. They can't add a switch to toggle back to the old animations because they're no longer available in the global file.</P><P>It's likely this will never change back until average system specs for graphics cards increase so they've got more memory to work with. And if that does happen they've shown more interest in adding fancy particle effects/zone textures/lighting effects to make use of the that extra memory (I shudder to think what EQ2 is going to need)</P><P>Anyway, get used to living with the current skel models as they're going to be with us for a while</P><P></P><P>Narben the Gnome Gnecro<BR>Colleague of Sanctuary<BR>Luclin server<BR>"Find your own damn witty comment"</font></td>
