      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Narben</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Why do people keep saying there used to be two models for the old skeleton pet? Is there ANYTHING that points to the dark bone pet as being a seperate model from the white bone? <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Yes, there was 2 types of graphic given to mob skeletons in the game, one white, one dark. Since the changes these mobs both now appear as the new skeleton model. The fact that they haven't allowed for switching back to the old model also shows that there would have been 2 choices.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>You telling me there are a fixed AMOUNT of slots in the file, ie 200 models? Or, each model takes say 4kb memory to load, and you can only have 1mb allocated for the global file? (theoretical values, just for example). If first is true they actually "nerfed" us (if you can nerf a class graphically :P), it just makes no sense. I remember them talking about adding jack'o'lanters and more to the global files, maybe time to remove them, or think how important it is to have dragons in the global file <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>The simplest answer is the second choice, yes there is a limit to the global file based on how much you can allocate to memory. The actual limit is determined by the size of a graphic cards memory, whatever they put on the side of the box as the minimum specs is the limit they have for loading graphics into memory (thats everything not just models). <BR>Some old time players with good recall may remember previous posts by Verant staff on the issue, it's been a while since they've talked about it. Historically Verant has been <b>extremely</b> unwilling to add extra animations to the global file. They've posted that opinion numerous times in response to Enchanters asking "why can't we have more illusions?". It's only as time moves on and the average system specs of players increase that they've been able to add extra models. With the release of Luclin they went for eye candy by increasing the polygon count of the models. Yes you can switch everything off but but be aware that the designers still have to assume a person will have everything switched on and allocate memory based on that assumption. Hence they trimmed the global models by removing skeletons. Was it fair? No. Is it worth getting all lathered over? No.</P><P>BTW dragons aren't global, they won't show up in every zone in the game<BR></font></td>
      </tr>
